I have been skinny most my growing years but in my later 20s I started gaining so much weight. Mostly because I filled up my life with insatiable amount of junk food and the stress of everyday life caught up to me. When I started my fitness journey I wasn’t sure what I was getting into. I hated running, never lifted weights and I am never the one to starve myself. So it was hard to find a balance for everything. I remember hating to go to the gym but feeling so good about myself after I came back. So that slowly became a routine and in 6 months I had lost like around 15 kgs of weight. It wasn’t about the scale, it wasn’t about how I fit into clothes or the mean comments that started coming my way when people saw me after a long time (maybe a little🤏🏻). It was about how I felt about myself. I remember walking up a hill in Shillong in 2023 and being so out of breath because how unfit I was. And this year when I climbed the same hill, I was fine. It was empowering !💪 

The most important thing that fitness teaches you is Action lead to Results. Giving me a little sense of control over my otherwise very unpredictable life. A sense of freedom, strength and so much confidence. 

So I tell myself and to every girl who is struggling with their body, you can change things only by believing in yourself. Never put yourself down because that is one judgment you can’t run away from. 

This is straight from my heart. Hugs and so much love🤗🫂
